               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t16871207-31-off145-c90" targOrder="Y" targets="t16871207-31-defend142 t16871207-31-off145 t16871207-31-verdict148"></join>
         
               <p>
            
               
                  <persName id="t16871207-31-defend142" type="defendantName">
                     John 
                     Waters
                  <interp inst="t16871207-31-defend142" type="surname" value="Waters"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16871207-31-defend142" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16871207-31-defend142" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , of <placeName id="t16871207-31-defloc144">St. Mary le Bone</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t16871207-31-defloc144" type="placeName" value="St. Mary le Bone"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t16871207-31-defloc144" type="type" value="defendantHome"></interp>
                  <join result="persNamePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t16871207-31-defend142 t16871207-31-defloc144"></join>, was Indicted for <rs id="t16871207-31-off145" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16871207-31-off145" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16871207-31-off145" type="offenceSubcategory" value="housebreaking"></interp>
               Breaking open the House of 
                     
                        <persName id="t16871207-31-victim144" type="victimName">
                           Jane 
                           Mason
                        <interp inst="t16871207-31-victim144" type="surname" value="Mason"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16871207-31-victim144" type="given" value="Jane"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16871207-31-victim144" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t16871207-31-off145 t16871207-31-victim144"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , between the hours of Twelve and one, on the <rs id="t16871207-31-cd146" type="crimeDate">12th. of May</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t16871207-31-off145 t16871207-31-cd146"></join> last, taking thence ten Pewter Tankards, value 17 s. four Pewter Tankards, value 4 s. one Iron Jack and Eleven Pound in money, numbered
            </rs>. Upon the Tryal it appeared, that Waters keeping a <rs id="t16871207-31-deflabel147" type="occupation">Publick House</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t16871207-31-defend142 t16871207-31-deflabel147"></join>, one Marshall (now in the Gate-house) left the goods at his House, pretending they were seized upon Execution, and that they were not concealed in the House, but lay as they were brought in bound up together. And testification being made, that he was an honest labouring man, he was brought in <rs id="t16871207-31-verdict148" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16871207-31-verdict148" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               not guilty
            </rs>.</p>
